article.description: Isaiah Miles scored 19 points and grabbed eight rebounds, James Demery added 17 points, and Saint Joseph's improved to 10-0 on the road with an 88-62 win over La Salle on Saturday night.
article.headline: Saint Joseph's dominates La Salle 88-62.
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Isaiah Miles scored 19 points and grabbed eight rebounds, James Demery added 17 points, and Saint Joseph's improved to 10-0 on the road with an 88-62 win over La Salle on Saturday night. Saint Joseph's (21-4, 10-2 Atlantic 10) dominated from start to finish, scoring the first nine points and leading by as many as 30 points in the second half. The Hawks have won three straight and 17 of 19. Miles made three 3-pointers as the Hawks combined to shoot 8 of 20 from behind the arc and 31 of 60 (52 percent) overall. DeAndre Bembry scored 13 points and collected nine rebounds. Cleon Roberts scored 17 points to lead La Salle (5-18, 1-11), which tied a season high with 13 3-pointers. Hawks coach Phil Martelli played 16 of the 17 players listed on the Saint Joseph's roster.
